verses.roman:
jhāṅkarā paryanta gela sei daśa jane
jhāṅkarāte pāila giyā vaiṣṇavera gaṇe

synonyms: jhāṅkarā paryanta—to the place known as Jhāṅkarā; gela—went; sei daśa jane—those ten men; jhāṅkarāte—at Jhāṅkarā; pāila—caught up to; giyā—going; vaiṣṇavera gaṇe—the group of Vaiṣṇavas.
translation: In Jhāṅkarā, the ten men caught up with the group of Vaiṣṇavas going to Nīlācala.
